articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Former Celtic manager Gordon Strachan has suggested that ‘neutral ball boys’ could aid Rangers’ cause against his old club in this Sunday’s Scottish Cup semi-final.
articles.title: 'Some things favour Rangers' - Ex-Celtic boss makes Hampden ball boys claim ahead of Scottish Cup semi-final

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: It isn’t just Celtic’s expected starring acts that have earned acclaim for the club’s scintillating form this season.
articles.title: Celtic star admits: 'I didn't know I was a player of the year candidate'

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: Few would rule out the possibility of peerless Celtic plunderer Kyogo Furuhashi finding Rangers’ net when the footballing behemoths battle for a place in the Scottish Cup final come Sunday. Few, though, are likely to appreciate the significance in the event of that happening.
articles.title: Celtic's Kyogo can surpass McCoist and Larsson with near 30-year derby first against Rangers

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: “No league structure is perfect but over the past two decades the split has become an established and exciting element of the cinch Premiership.” The SPFL’s chief operating officer Calum Beattie perfectly summed up a curious element of the Scottish Premiership.
articles.title: Premiership split fixtures: Celtic-Rangers title intrigue, Europe battle set up nicely, relegation excitement but Sky fan criticism

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Celtic manager Ange Postecoglou had admitted that he would have preferred not to have been handed two consecutive away matches after the Premiership split.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou reveals gripe with Celtic post-split fixtures - 'it is what it is'

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Chelsea are set to appoint a new manager and could do so by the end of this week – while Ange Postecoglou has been linked with West Ham.
articles.title: Chelsea set for new boss, Ange Postecoglou link, Australian told to stay at 'way better' Celtic over West Ham

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Celtic will be able to clinch the Scottish Premiership title a week on Sunday when they face Hearts at Tynecastle Park after the SPFL confirmed the post-split fixtures.
articles.title: Premiership split fixtures announced: Rangers v Celtic, Hearts v Aberdeen, relegation battle, key dates

articles.author: Chris Andrews
articles.description: Celtic could win the Scottish Premiership title at Hearts with the SPFL set to send the league leaders to Tynecastle Park in the first round of the split, according to reports.
articles.title: Celtic set for title chance at Tynecastle Park - Hearts v Aberdeen unlikely to be on TV, Rangers v Celtic date

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: It is a perturbing situation Rangers and Michael Beale suddenly find themselves in.
articles.title: The danger of Michael Beale becoming Rangers version of Celtic’s Neil Lennon, and need to be radical with keeper and striker selections at Hampden

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Chris Sutton has labelled Rangers’ Scottish Cup semi-final with Celtic on Sunday as “an enormous game”, claiming the Ibrox club have been guilty of ending up with “massive egg on their face" in the rivalry.
articles.title: Ex-Celtic makes Rangers 'massive egg on face' claim over rivalry - as Chris Sutton gives Michael Beale praise

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Rangers legend Ally McCoist believes Celtic star Kyogo Furuhashi plays in a similar fashion to Manchester City’s hot shot striker Erling Halland.
articles.title: Rangers legend compares Celtic ace with Erling Haaland - but skirts Alfredo Morelos question

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Willie Collum will referee Rangers v Celtic on Sunday as the Scottish FA confirmed the officials for the Scottish Cup semi-finals.
articles.title: Rangers v Celtic referee and VAR confirmed as SFA reveal Scottish Cup semi-finals officials, Old Firm record

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Celtic and Rangers face an injury sweat in the coming week over key players ahead of the Scottish Cup semi-final meeting on Sunday at Hampden Park.
articles.title: Rangers v Celtic team news: 5 Old Firm stars doubts for Scottish Cup semi, one Ibrox ace out, Postecoglou hint

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: Former Manchester City and England defender Micah Richards believes it is “only a matter of time” before a Premier League makes a move for Celtic boss Ange Postecoglou.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou to Chelsea: Popular pundit makes 'only matter of time' Premier League claim over Celtic boss

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Kevin van Veen is one of Scotland’s most colourful characters, as well as being a pretty adept striker. His goal for Motherwell that earned them a 1-1 draw at Celtic Park was his 24th of the season and helped his team become the first to take points from Parkhead this season. And in his usual honest manner, the Dutchman explained exactly how you do it.
articles.title: Kevin van Veen bares all in revealing interview - how to stop Celtic, Kyogo, 30 goals and leaving Motherwell

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Tomoki Iwata believes Celtic will regroup and right the wrongs of a 1-1 draw with Motherwell in time for Sunday’s huge Scottish Cup semi-final clash against Rangers.
articles.title: Tomoki Iwata reveals where Celtic went wrong and why it won't be same against Rangers

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: We pick out three observations from Celtic’s 1-1 draw with Motherwell as the champions-in-waiting failed to win at home for the first time this season...
articles.title: Celtic reaction: Treble concerns, Parkhead persona non grata, record hopes intact

articles.author: Aidan Smith
articles.description: I haven’t always been a sports reporter. Pipe down, all those hollering: “We didnae ken you ever were!” My first match viewed from the pressbox, though, was a 12.15pm semi-final for Inverness Caley Thistle just about the length of the country from the Highlands, so all those fans trekking to Hampden on Saturday for such an ungodly kick-off, I feel your pain.
articles.title: Welcome to Hampden, let me show you to your seat - actually just take the whole row

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Celtic captain Callum McGregor is hopeful Ange Postecoglou will remain at Parkhead amid reports that the Australian is on the shortlist to become next Chelsea manager.
articles.title: Celtic's Callum McGregor responds to Ange Postecoglou Chelsea speculation - 'we want to keep him'

articles.author: John Fallon
articles.description: Outgoing head coach Mike Blair has admitted that a squad with Edinburgh’s talent should not be finishing in the lower reaches of the URC.
articles.title: Mike Blair: Edinburgh should not be finishing in lower reaches of URC with this squad

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: So Celtic are human after all. The unstoppable Ange Postecoglou winning machine broke down for the first time at Celtic Park this season as the hosts were held to a surprise 1-1 draw by Motherwell.
articles.title: So this is how you stop Celtic: concerns creep in with Jota and Reo Hatate situation, mighty Motherwell

articles.author: Matthew Elder
articles.description: Ange Postecoglou admitted Celtic face a more challenging build-up to their Scottish Cup semi-final against Rangers after falling below their usual standards in being held to a surprise 1-1 draw by Motherwell.
articles.title: Ange Postecoglou admits Celtic now face Rangers ‘challenge’ after dropping standards

articles.author: Joel Sked
articles.description: The Premiership now splits into two after this weekend’s action with the final three teams confirmed following the five Saturday matches.
articles.title: Premiership split: When are fixtures announced, key dates, Rangers v Celtic, Euro situation, relegation battle

articles.description: Neil Lennon has opened up on his regrets during his last season in charge of Celtic.
articles.title: Neil Lennon opens up on Celtic regrets - 'I could've maybe done things a little differently but it was unprecedented'

articles.author: Mark Atkinson
articles.description: Former Celtic manager Neil Lennon has recalled just how close the club came to signing Ivan Toney.
articles.title: Ivan Toney: How close Celtic came to signing Brentford and England hitman

articles.author: Andrew Smith
articles.description: It is fair to say Steven MacLean has been bowled over by the all-consuming nature of football management since being placed in charge of St Johnstone on an interim basis. That doesn’t mean he is over bowls, though.
articles.title: The Scottish Premiership manager who won't give up bowls for anything

articles.description: Imagine a scenario where Celtic finish the season 12 points ahead of Rangers but are not declared champions. Instead, the top six go into a play-off series to determine the title winners.
